There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/a8f48032-2801-4aa8-bad7-bfac2803af63/to/562c87b2-d78e-46c8-b3e7-c3180478ead0) against commit 9cbd6ff10159d1130ddbcc161c5e8d2b2b5006a2:
```diff
  Benchmark                                                   Metric          Change
  ============================================================================================
+ build                                                       aesop           -39.9%
- build                                                       linting          21.7%
- build                                                       parsing          27.8%
- build                                                       wall-clock        7.0%
- open Mathlib                                                instructions    114.4% (209.6 σ)
- open Mathlib                                                task-clock     1016.5%  (25.0 σ)
- open Mathlib                                                wall-clock      234.8% (202.2 σ)
+ ~Mathlib.Algebra.Exact                                      instructions     -6.7%
- ~Mathlib.Algebra.Homology.HomotopyCategory.SingleFunctors   instructions     21.3%
+ ~Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Morphisms.RingHomProperties      instructions    -10.3%
+ ~Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.ProjectiveSpectrum.Scheme        instructions     -5.9%
+ ~Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Restrict                         instructions     -5.9%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.DifferentialObject                  instructions     -8.1%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.GradedObject.Trifunctor             instructions     -3.8%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Cones                        instructions     -4.4%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Shapes.Diagonal              instructions     -7.9%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Linear.FunctorCategory              instructions    -10.0%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Comon_                     instructions     -6.6%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Internal.FunctorCategory   instructions     -9.2%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Mon_                       instructions     -6.2%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.MorphismProperty.Factorization      instructions    -10.0%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Preadditive.EilenbergMoore          instructions    -10.1%
+ ~Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Preadditive.EndoFunctor             instructions     -7.5%
+ ~Mathlib.Geometry.RingedSpace.PresheafedSpace.Gluing        instructions     -3.9%
+ ~Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.TensorProduct.Graded.External        instructions     -5.2%
+ ~Mathlib.NumberTheory.RamificationInertia                   instructions     -4.7%
+ ~Mathlib.RepresentationTheory.Action.Basic                  instructions     -9.2%
+ ~Mathlib.RepresentationTheory.GroupCohomology.Resolution    instructions     -4.3%
+ ~Mathlib.RingTheory.Kaehler                                 instructions     -5.7%
```
So Aesop is much faster and the overall build much slower? Perhaps we should benchmark against `2c5ea133761ae723a6bce63dc236560fdcd6e17e` to minimise interference from other commits.

[Here](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/8c43b26a-1ee7-4164-8aba-f42d7c2f8c75/to/562c87b2-d78e-46c8-b3e7-c3180478ead0) is the comparison between `lean-pr-testing-4478` and this PR. This should isolate the impact of turning on precompilation in Aesop. TLDR:

- Aesop -40%
- build wall-clock +7%
- interpretation +10%
- `open Mathlib` task-clock +1000%, wall-clock +225%, instructions +109%

So a loss overall. But where do these crazy numbers for `open Mathlib` come from? And why does interpretation get slower?

> But where do these crazy numbers for open Mathlib come from?

This is likely because a no-op `lake build` suddenly takes 10x as much time on my machine. /cc @tydeu

@Kha I think this may be due to nature of precompile modules implying transitive import computation ([lake#132](https://github.com/leanprover/lake/pull/132)), but I will need to investigate this further.
Closing; new attempt at #19055

pullRequest.title: chore: bump Aesop to enable precompilation
